text: A Practical Guide to Astral Projection is an EP and the second studio record by American rock band The Nymphs. It was produced by Bill Price and released in 1992 on DGC Records. The EP consists of demos of "The Highway" and "Alright" the band made prior to being signed, a previously unreleased cover of Badfinger's "Come and Get It" plus the album versions of "Imitating Angels" and "Wasting My Days". The EP was released after the band broke up.
